# Managed vs. external tables

Every UC table is one flavour or the other — and it decides ownership, `DROP`, and features.

## The split

- **Managed** — UC owns metadata **and** files (UC-managed location); `DROP` deletes both after retention
- **External** — UC owns metadata; files at **your** path; `DROP` removes metadata only, **files stay**

## What managed gets that external doesn't

- **Predictive Optimization** ✅ (external ❌)
- Full UC lifecycle management

## Choosing & converting

- **Exam default: prefer managed.** Go external only for a multi-tool lake, files made outside Databricks, or a regulator-fixed path
- **`ALTER TABLE … SET MANAGED / SET EXTERNAL`** — metadata-level on UC; three-part name unchanged; files may move; needs storage-location privileges
